Commentary Text: S Kaul to Rayudu, out Rayudu Run Out!! 1 run completed. What just happened there? "One of the very best from Rayudu," says Sanjay Manjrekar on air and I couldn't agree more. He lifts the back of a length delivery on the bounce to long-off, settles with a single as Pandey lobs the ball back to Kaul, who fumbles and Rayudu thought there was a chance to steal a second. Raina stands his ground and by the time Rayudu turns back, Kaul gets to the ball and throws it to KW to remove the bails. There was never a second and Rayudu knew that, he walks up to Raina with a smile on his face, hugs him and trudges off to a standing ovation. Rayudu run out (S Kaul/Williamson) 79(37) [4s-9 6s-4]

Commentary Text: Chahar to Manish Pandey, out Caught by Karn Sharma!! That's the second duck of this innings. First it was Bhui and now it's Manish. Was a full length delivery outside off and swinging away from the batsman, Manish went ahead with his shot and ended up slicing it to the man at third man. Surprising to see that it carried all the way to third man. Probably there was a bit of extra bounce on that. Manish Pandey c Karn Sharma b Chahar 0(2)
